{
  "local_port": 39302,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply for improvement in the 12th CBSE exam?",
  "response": "If you wish to apply for **Improvement** in the 12th CBSE (Central Board of Secondary Education) exam, you can take the exam again to improve your scores in one or more subjects. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you apply for improvement:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Eligibility for Improvement**  \n- You can apply for improvement if you have already appeared for the 12th CBSE exam but want to improve your marks in one or more subjects.\n- You can apply as a **Private Candidate** or through your school, depending on your situation.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Choose the Subjects**  \n- You can choose to improve marks in **one or more subjects**.\n- You can also reappear for **all subjects**, but this is optional.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Apply Through Your School or as a Private Candidate**  \n- **Through Your School**:  \n  - If you are still enrolled in the same school, you can apply for the improvement exam through your school.  \n  - Submit a written application to your school principal stating your desire to reappear for the improvement exam.\n\n- **As a Private Candidate**:  \n  - If you have left school or are no longer enrolled, you can apply as a private candidate.  \n  - Download the application form from the CBSE website and submit it to the regional CBSE office along with the required documents and fees.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Application Process**  \n- Obtain the application form for the improvement exam from your school or the CBSE website.\n- Fill in the required details, including the subjects you want to improve.\n- Attach the necessary documents:\n  - Original mark sheet of the previous exam.\n  - Aadhaar card or other ID proof.\n  - Passport-sized photographs.\n- Pay the examination fees (varies depending on the number of subjects).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Submit the Application**  \n- Submit the completed application form and documents to your school or the CBSE regional office, depending on your status (school candidate or private candidate).\n- Ensure you meet the **application deadline**.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Prepare for the Exam**  \n- Focus on the subjects you want to improve.  \n- Use previous year question papers, NCERT books, and other study materials for preparation.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Appear for the Exam**  \n- The improvement exam is usually conducted along with the regular CBSE board exams (March/April).\n- Private candidates will receive their admit cards from the CBSE regional office.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Result and Mark Sheet**  \n- After the exam, your result will be declared along with the regular CBSE results.\n- The final mark sheet will reflect the improved marks in the subjects you reappeared for.\n\n---\n\n### Important Points to Note:  \n- Your original marksheet will remain valid even if you appear for improvement.\n- You can take the improvement exam **only once** in the next academic session (e.g., if you appeared in 2024, you can reappear in 2025).\n- The improved marks will be considered for higher education or job applications.\n\n---\n\nFor more details, visit the official CBSE website: [www.cbse.gov.in](http://www.cbse.gov.in) or contact your school/regional CBSE office.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
